Dialogue: 3,0:00:11.82,0:00:16.32,Callout,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(640,112)\fs21\c&H00988F8A&}// VISUAL: A BIG AMBER NUMBER BEING POURED INTO A SMALL\NBOX THAT...
Dialogue: 3,0:00:34.53,0:00:39.03,Callout,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(640,112)\fs21\c&H00988F8A&}// SIDE-BY-SIDE: ARIANE 4 GENTLE CURVE VS ARIANE 5 STEEP\NCURVE; THE...
Dialogue: 10,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.91,Caption,,0,0,0,,But at one point, the code needed to\Nhand that
Dialogue: 10,0:00:03.91,0:00:07.42,Caption,,0,0,0,,value to another part of the system that\Nexpected
Dialogue: 10,0:00:07.42,0:00:10.94,Caption,,0,0,0,,something smaller — a sixteen-bit\Nnumber. A far smaller
Dialogue: 10,0:00:10.94,0:00:11.33,Caption,,0,0,0,,box.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:11.67,0:00:15.51,Caption,,0,0,0,,And here is the entire disaster, in one\Nidea: on
Dialogue: 10,0:00:15.51,0:00:19.35,Caption,,0,0,0,,Ariane 4, the sideways speed never got\Nbig enough to
Dialogue: 10,0:00:19.35,0:00:23.19,Caption,,0,0,0,,overflow that little box. The rocket was\Nslower off the
Dialogue: 10,0:00:23.19,0:00:25.11,Caption,,0,0,0,,pad. The number always fit.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:25.45,0:00:29.74,Caption,,0,0,0,,Ariane 5 was a different animal. More\Npowerful. It built
Dialogue: 10,0:00:29.74,0:00:33.61,Caption,,0,0,0,,up horizontal speed far faster than its\Npredecessor ever
Dialogue: 10,0:00:33.61,0:00:34.04,Caption,,0,0,0,,could.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:34.38,0:00:37.82,Caption,,0,0,0,,Thirty-seven seconds into the flight,\Nthat sideways speed
Dialogue: 10,0:00:37.82,0:00:42.13,Caption,,0,0,0,,climbed past the largest value the small\Nbox could hold.
